extends layout

block content
  .container
    h1 Welcome to #{title}!
    
    ul.steps.list-unstyled
      // Welcome
      li.well
        p This is the first time you are accessing #{title}. To make sure everything is working the way you want it to, you're guided through this little assistant.
        p It will walk you through setting up an admin account and will enable you to adjust defaults.
        
        btn#setup-begin.btn.btn-success Begin Setup
      // Admin user
      li.well
        h3 #1: Admin user
        p There is no admin user yet. This type of user is able to change everything, including the system's configuration and the list of users, that have access to the room.
        p You should now specify a unique yet simple username for the admin user and a <b>strong</b> password only you know.
        
        .panel.panel-default
          .panel-heading Admin User
          .panel-body
            form.form.form-horizontal
              .form-group
                label.control-label.col-sm-3(for="setup-admin-username") Username
                .col-sm-9
                  input.form-control(type="text", id="setup-admin-username", placeholder="Username")
              .form-group
                label.control-label.col-sm-3(for="setup-admin-password") Password
                .col-sm-9
                  input.form-control(type="password", id="setup-admin-password", placeholder="Strong password")
              .form-group
                label.control-label.col-sm-3(for="setup-admin-password-repeat") Repeat password
                .col-sm-9
                  input.form-control(type="password", id="setup-admin-password-repeat", placeholder="Repeat the strong password")
                  
              .form-group
                span.help-block Enter the text you defined to identify as the system admin:
                label.control-label.col-sm-3(for="setup-admin-control") Control text
                .col-sm-9
                  input.form-control(type="text", id="setup-admin-control", placeholder="Control text")
              
              .form-actions
                btn#setup-save-admin.btn.btn-default Next Step
      // Initial settings
      li.well
        h3 #2: General settings
        p Great!
        p Now that you can log into the application, why don't we set the settings right away so you can focus on using the application right away?
        p Right, here are some options for you:
        
        .panel.panel-default
          .panel-heading Settings
          .panel-body
            form.form.form-horizontal
              h4.help-block Database
              .form-group
                label.control-label.col-sm-3(for="setup-db-name") Database name
                .col-sm-9
                  input.form-control(type="text", id="setup-db-name", placeholder="db.sqlite")
              .form-group
                label.control-label.col-sm-3(for="setup-db-username") Database username
                .col-sm-9
                  input.form-control(type="text", id="setup-db-name", placeholder="admin")
              .form-group
                label.control-label.col-sm-3(for="setup-db-password") Database password
                .col-sm-9
                  input.form-control(type="text", id="setup-db-password", placeholder="admin")
                  
              // TODO: add way more settings, and validate if the database settings are even needed
              
              .form-actions
                btn#setup-back-admin.btn.btn-default Back
                btn#setup-save-settings.btn.btn-default Finish setup
                
      // Save settings, then redirect
      li.well
        h3 #3: Send new defaults
        p Just a second and you'll be ready to go!
        p We are currently uploading the new settings to the server who is then processing it.
        
        p If everything is ready, click this button:
        
        a#setup-end.btn.btn-success(href="/") Go to login page!
    
  
  script(src="/js/setup.js")
